# Cursor Optimization Rules

# Disable unnecessary features for faster performance
- Don't auto-index large directories
- Skip analysis of node_modules, .venv, __pycache__
- Limit file watching to active files only
- Disable unused language servers

# Python-specific optimizations
- Only index Python files in active workspace
- Skip type checking for files not in use
- Limit Pyright memory usage

# Git optimizations
- Don't watch .git directory
- Limit git status checks

# File watching
- Exclude large directories from file watchers
- Limit simultaneous file operations
